1. e4
1. c6 {I propose two plans for studying this course.   • Plan 1 (below 1800 chess.com/2000 Lichess):‣Focus on the 'Advance Variation Sidelines' and worry less about4.dxc5(ideally just check after each game anyone plays it against you by using the move trainer from the course).‣Exchange Variation: Focus on the1.e4c62.d4d53.exd5cxd54.Nf3Nc65.Nc3and5.Bb5lines while you can fill the gaps of the main lines later as you improve.‣Classical Variation: Focus on the Tartakower with6.Nf3and skip the subtle6.c3.‣Two Knights: Literally skip this line! Below 1800 they rarely play5.Qe2and usually just transpose into the Tartakower.‣Panov Attack: Simply learn the first two trainables of the chapter and move on!‣Fantasy Variation: Learn everything besides the mainline with5.Nc3.‣d3 lines: Skip this part!‣Other Sidelines: go over your favorite Hillbilly Attack and get the heck out of here!• Plan 2 (above 1800): ‣lock yourself inside the house, take a break with your partner because it's time to study hard! No shortcuts for you, just gotta go all-in and study everything if you want to be a champ!} 
