[Black "Chessable Note: Three-Tiered Approach to Learning"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]
[Result "*"]

 {This course offers students a three-tiered approach to learning. You can naturally progress from one tier to the next depending on your ambition, level, and intended purpose for this opening in your repertoire. Many students may decide the first or first two tiers suffice for their preparation, and will use the rest of the course as a reference source to keep coming back to and consult as their experience with the opening grows.Tier 1: Includes 7 trainable lines presented in the Quickstarter Guide chapter. This is a quick overview which will give you a good general idea of the repertoire, and allow your to start  trying out the repertoire in some games, but of course will still leave many holes, especially for things that you are likely to face less frequently.Tier 2: Includes “Priority Lines” which have been handpicked by the author as being particularly instructive and/or likely to have high relevance in many of your games. They include a broader coverage of the most important material throughout the chapters, where these lines show with variation titles in bold.Tier 3: the entire 150+ trainable variations of the course.If you wish to start out your studying by just focusing on Tiers 1 and 2, the right-hand Settings menu in the course enables you to set your Learn setting from “Everything” to “Priority Only”. Which will allow you to study and review only the hand-picked priority lines in the course chapters.Tips:  You can switch the Learn setting from 'Priority Only' to “Everything” at any point later. If you choose to focus on Priority Lines first, you may find your studying experience smoother if you also select to Study “All Moves” rather than just “Key Moves”.} 1. --
