6. Bf5 {This was a tough call. Objectively speaking, if you can remember it, Sielecki's6...h5!is best and I had a lot of fun playing it. However, from my experience it could be challenging to remember such small details when you are starting out your Caro-Kann journey, and for this reason I decided to stick with the standard approach, hopefully making it easier to remember.So my recommendation would be to start with6...Bf5and when you are comfortable enough, you could start messing around with6...h5!?} 
