8. Bxd3
9. Qxd3
9. Nge7 {Preparing to play ...Nf5 next while staying away from9...Be7, which gets a lot of beginners in trouble because the g8-knight is stuck after that!} 
10. Nge2
10. Nf5
11. O-O
11. Be7
12. a3
12. O-O {We can continue with ...Rc8 followed by ...a6-b5 ➼ putting pressure on the queenside with ...Na5-Nc4 ideas.} 
