7. Nf5 {This move is important because it stops Be3 ideas, while preparing ...Ng3 in case White goes h3. Besides that, we can simply play ...e6 next followed by picking up the c5-pawn.8.e6!?In case White does not find this, they are simply worse (which is quite surprising on move 8 if you'd ask me).8...Bxf39.Bxf3fxe610.O-Og6We need to get developed somehow.11.Re1Bg712.Rxe6Ncd413.Re1Qc7=We are ready to pick up the c5-pawn and then finish development with ...O-O!} 
