9. Qe2 {This move is very natural, simply preparing to play Be3 ➼ developing, gaining a tempo while preparing to castle short. The funny story is that I've actually encountered this move once and then I was really kicking myself for not knowing Black's best move because it's something of pure beauty.} 
9. Nd4 {That made me jump out of my chair the first time I saw the computer recommending it. What makes it so special is the fact that it's the move that you would expect the least!The main point is that 9.Qe2 has left the c1-bishop undefended, and10.cxd4Qxc1+is good for Black.} 
10. Qf2
10. Nxf3+
11. gxf3
11. Qxf2+
12. Kxf2
12. Bf5 {We can meet13.Bb5+with13...Bd7with at least an equal game.} 
