7. e6 {This move is somewhat 'safer' in case you want an alternative to7...Qa5+!?} 
8. Be3
8. d4 {Simply winning back the c5-pawn. The drawback of this move is that strategically speaking, Black needs to be careful after weakening the e4-c4 squares which can potentially be occupied effectively by White's minor pieces.} 
9. Bf2
9. Bxc5 {Already creating a positional threat of meeting10.O-Owith10...Nf5!followed by ...Ne3 with very annoying counterplay.} 
10. Nbd2 {This is always an option for White, especially after playing Be3 because that's usually a sign that White is preparing to play Nbd2 (without blocking the c1-bishop) to be able to take back on f3 with the knight.} 
10. Nf5 {The timing is really important. Else the positional concession with pushing ...d4 can backfire pretty badly.} 
11. h3
11. Ne3 {The first unusual move to remember.} 
12. Bxe3
12. Bxf3 {This is the point! Make sure to study the move orders carefully if you are planning to use this line.} 
13. Qxf3
13. dxe3 {At this point White has a choice, but Black should be fine regardless.} 
14. Nb3 {This seems to be White's best try according to the computer.14.Ne4looks far more natural, but it's not ideal:14...Bb4+!After this important check White has a hard time coordinating.Keep in mind that15.Ke2Nd4+!wins for Black unlike in the 14.Nb3! line.15.Kf1Qb6Simply protecting the e3-pawn.16.c3Be717.b4O-O-O∞With ideas such as ...g5/f5 looming, White needs to be really careful not to lose immediately.} 
14. Nd4 {This idea is critical to get a straightforward path to equality.The tempting14...Bb4+is less effective here because of15.Ke2and White is chilling.} 
15. Nxd4
15. Qxd4
16. Qxb7
16. O-O {Black manages to hide the king into a safe position while creating a multitude of threats. At this point White is pretty much forced to play it safe and go for the endgame.} 
17. Qe4
17. Qxe4
18. Bxe4
18. Rab8
19. b3 {19.O-O-O ?Rb4!⩱wins the f4-pawn.} 
19. f6 {It's important to become active, otherwise we can get squeezed.} 
20. exf6
20. Rxf6 {With a holdable endgame. White has two plans:A)21.g3g5!22.fxg5?!Rf2!23.O-O-OBa3+24.Kb1Bb425.Rde1Bd2!and Black is better.B)21.Rf1Rb422.c4Rb823.Ke2Rd824.Rad1Rxd125.Kxd1g5!26.g3e527.f5Ra628.a4Rh629.Rh1a5with a comfortable draw.} 
