10. O-O-O {This is the most common move for White by far.10.c3Nc7Now that ...Nb4 is no longer a thing ➼ we are preparing to play ...Nd5 next.11.O-O-ONd512.Rhe1Be613.Kb1b5∓This is a critical move which  reinforces the d5-knight because there will be no c4-ideas. On the next move we can play ...Qa5 which creates a huge threat of ...Nxe3 followed by ...Qxa2+!10.Bxa6, giving up the bishop pair, is definitely double edged.10...bxa611.O-OBg4Creating a huge positional threat of ...Bxf3!12.Ne1Bc7=We can continue with ...Qd6 next and Black gets good attacking chances against the enemy king. The bishop pair compensates for the ruined pawn structure.} 
