12. Bf8 {Keeping the bishop pair and playing around the f5-knight for a little while.} 
13. Bd2 {13.Bf4This move could easily get White in trouble.13...Nd5!14.Bg3?g6!White does not have a good square for the knight.15.Ne3Rxe3!16.fxe3Nxe317.Qe2Nxf118.Rxf1f5∓With a clean extra pawn for Black.} 
13. Be6
14. Rfe1
14. Nd5 {Centralizing and preparing to push ...b5! It is important to understand that15.c4Nb4!wins the bishop pair.} 
15. a3
15. b5
16. b3
16. a5
17. c4
