11. Qd2 {This seems to be the most critical move.11.Qc2Be612.Rad1Rc8!?Placing the rook behind the enemy queen while preparing the typical battery with ...Bb8-Qc7!13.Nc3Bb814.Rfe1h5⇆Considering ...Qc7 followed by ...h4 ideas next, with pressure against the enemy king.11.Ng3g6!Stopping Nf5 ideas.12.Qd2f5Threatening ...Qh4, and then ...f4 is hard to stop.13.Ne2Ne614.Rad1Qc715.f4b6=We can continue with ...Bb7 followed by ...Rad8 and Black is very solid.11.Nc3f5!Stopping Ne4 ideas!12.Qd2h6Preparing to play ...Qf6 without allowing any Bg5 ideas.13.Rfe1Qf614.f4b615.Rad1Bb7=We can continue with ...Rad8 followed by ...Ne6-Bf8 with a very solid position for Black.} 
