8. Qf4 {This seems to be by far the most played move.8.Qe3h69.Ne4Bxe4!It's important to stay away from9...Nd7??10.Nd6#which ends the game immediately.10.Qxe4Nd711.Bc4e612.d4Nf613.Qd3Bd6Stopping White from playing Bf4.14.O-OQc715.h3O-O16.Be3Rfd8=We are ready to break with ...c5 next, so Black is perfectly fine. Another interesting idea to keep in mind is that Black can usually play something like ...Bh2+ (forcing White's king in the corner) followed by ...Bf4, which gets rid of the bishop pair. This is a common maneuver for such positions.} 
