4. Bc5 {Immediately taking control over the vulnerable diagonal. Black's plan is to follow up with ...Qb6 and White could get in huge trouble!} 
5. exd5 {This is a common mistake for lower rated players.5.Nc3!This is the only move to fight for an edge as White. The point is to meet 5...Qb6 with the difficult move to find 6.Na4! and White is doing well.5...Ne7I recommend we abandon the mission before it's too late and stick to normal play.6.f4This is one of the best variations for White, given by Levy Rozman in his comprehensive 1.e4 course!6...Qb67.Nf3Bf2+8.Ke2a5∞This move is important so we can meet 9.Na4 with 9...Qa7 leading to a complicated position. For more, make sure to check out the trainables!} 
5. Qb6 {Leaving White with a very unpleasant choice.} 
6. Ne2 {6.Nh3This is the lesser evil.6...Bxh37.gxh3Bf2+8.Ke2cxd59.Qxd5Nc6=∞With ...Rd8 and ...Bg1 ideas, White needs to be extra careful not to get mated in a blink.} 
6. Bf2+
7. Kd2
7. Qe3 {Enjoy.} 
