5. Nc3 {This is White's only move to fight for an advantage. The point is to meet5...Qb6with6.Na4!and White is getting a small edge with precise play!5.Bd3leads to a comfortable endgame for Black after5...dxe46.Bxe4Qxd1+7.Kxd1Be6, preparing to play ...Nd7 without blocking the light-squared bishop.8.Nd2Nd79.f4Nh6=∞We are going to castle long followed by the ...f6 break (while keeping ...Ng4 ideas).5.Ne2Nd76.Bf4In case of6.exd5the reply6...Nxe5gives Black a good position.6...Qb6⩱With a multitude of threats such as ...Bf2+ and ...Qxb2 with a small advantage for Black already.5.Bf4Qb6∓Attacking both the g1-knight and the b2-pawn with a much better position for Black already.} 
