2. d5
3. Bb2 {Gambiting the e4-pawn. This is White's main idea.3.Qe2!?This is a very interesting way of playing for White (perhaps the best try), but definitely quite rare.3...dxe44.Nc3Nf65.Nxe4Nxe46.Qxe4Qa5!This move is really useful because it prepares to solve the issue of our light-squared bishop with ...Bf5, and we can follow this up with another key idea: to play ...e6-Ba3 (exchanging White's most important piece).7.Bb2Bf58.Qc4e6=0-1 Reprintsev,A(2353)-Gunina,V(2427)Titled Tuesday intern op 23rd Mar Chess.com INT blitz 2021(2)We can continue with ...Nd7 and ...O-O-O, while White is having a hard time castling long because of ...Qxa2!3.exd5does not really make any sense when combined with b3, but it seems to be common for online games. We can basically look at this as an improved version of the 'Exchange Variation'.3...cxd54.Bb2Nc65.Nf3Bg46.Be2e67.O-ONf68.h3Bh5There is no particular reason to give up the bishop, so it's best to just keep the tension. If you are looking to simplify your strategy below 1500 online blitz you could always take on f3 in this kind of 'Exchange structure', but above that you will start to feel more the importance of having the bishop pair.9.d3Bd610.Nbd2O-O11.a3a5⩱We can continue with ...Re8-Rc8 followed by the ...e5-push. White's position is pretty cramped.} 
